msContents.summary: This manuscript contains excerpts from De viris illustribus (On Famous Men); excerpts from the Supplementum chronicarum; excerpts from the Vita Henrici Quinti (Life of Henry V); excerpts from works on Venice; and Peter Carmelianus, Rumores e venetiis allati fidelissimis auctoribus.

history.provenance: Owned by Joseph Mayner of Exeter College, ca. 1600; Duke of Suffolk (not traced in his sales); sold by Rodd to Sir Thomas Phillipps in 1845, no. 11580 (not traced in his sales); London sale, no. 674; English bookseller's catalogue, no. 307; John Frederick Lewis, Philadelphia; given by his widow, Anne Baker Lewis, to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1936
